---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Smart Lock Engineering Hub - Technical resources for smart lock deployment, protocols, and security"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <article class="prose prose-lg mx-auto">
      <h1>About Smart Lock Engineering Hub</h1>
      
      <p class="lead">
        Your trusted source for in-depth smart lock technical information, deployment guides, 
        and engineering resources.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        Smart Lock Engineering Hub exists to provide accurate, unbiased technical information 
        about smart lock systems, wireless protocols, security architecture, and deployment 
        strategies. We serve engineers, IT professionals, property managers, and technical 
        decision-makers who need detailed, actionable information.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Offer</h2>
      
      <h3>Comprehensive Technical Guides</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Protocol Analysis</strong> - Deep dives into Zigbee, Z-Wave, Wi-Fi, Thread, and Matter</li>
        <li><strong>Security Architecture</strong> - Threat modeling, encryption mechanisms, and compliance</li>
        <li><strong>Deployment Guides</strong> - Installation, troubleshooting, and best practices</li>
        <li><strong>Use Case Solutions</strong> - Industry-specific deployment strategies</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Interactive Tools</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Protocol Selection Wizard</strong> - Match your requirements to the right protocol</li>
        <li><strong>TCO Calculator</strong> - Calculate true lifetime costs</li>
        <li><strong>Battery Life Comparison</strong> - Compare power consumption across protocols</li>
        <li><strong>Compatibility Checker</strong> - Verify door and lock compatibility</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our Approach</h2>
      <p>
        We prioritize:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Technical Accuracy</strong> - Information backed by specifications, testing, and real-world deployments</li>
        <li><strong>Vendor Neutrality</strong> - Unbiased analysis across all major platforms and protocols</li>
        <li><strong>Practical Focus</strong> - Actionable guidance for real-world implementations</li>
        <li><strong>Continuous Updates</strong> - Regular content refresh as technology evolves</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Content Standards</h2>
      <p>
        Every article and tool on this site is:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Written by engineers with hands-on smart lock experience</li>
        <li>Based on manufacturer specifications and testing</li>
        <li>Reviewed for technical accuracy</li>
        <li>Updated to reflect current technology</li>
        <li>Free from marketing bias</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who We Serve</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Engineers & Architects</strong> - Designing smart lock systems</li>
        <li><strong>IT Professionals</strong> - Deploying and managing access control</li>
        <li><strong>Property Managers</strong> - Multi-unit residential and commercial</li>
        <li><strong>Hospitality Operations</strong> - Hotels, vacation rentals, co-working spaces</li>
        <li><strong>Technical Buyers</strong> - Making informed purchasing decisions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For technical questions, corrections, or suggestions:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Technical Issues</strong> - Report errors or outdated information</li>
        <li><strong>Content Requests</strong> - Suggest topics for new articles or tools</li>
        <li><strong>Partnerships</strong> - Industry collaboration opportunities</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        Smart Lock Engineering Hub provides technical information for educational purposes. 
        Always consult manufacturer specifications, local regulations, and qualified professionals 
        for specific deployment decisions. We are not affiliated with any smart lock manufacturer.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-12 rounded-lg bg-blue-50 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">Ready to Learn More?</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">
          Explore our comprehensive guides and interactive tools.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a
            href="/protocols"
            class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-primary-600 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-primary-700"
          >
            Browse Protocols
          </a>
          <a
            href="/tools"
            class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md border border-gray-300 bg-white px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50"
          >
            Try Our Tools
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
